Task 1: Cloud Storage Setup Using AWS S3

This task focuses on creating and configuring a reliable cloud storage system using Amazon Web Services (AWS) S3.

Objective

Set up a scalable and secure S3 bucket, implement file upload, configure access permissions, enable data protection features, and simulate storage lifecycle automation.

What I Did

- Created an AWS S3 bucket with a unique name and selected region
- Uploaded sample files (e.g., `.txt`, `.pdf`, `.jpg`)
- Enabled versioning for backup and recovery
- Configured bucket policy (JSON) to control access
- Enabled default server-side encryption (SSE-S3)
- Set up lifecycle rules to move files to Glacier after 30 days
- Took screenshots and documented each step


